         <abstract>
            <p>
               The theorem proved here extends the author's previous work on Chebyshev series [4] by showing that if $f(x)$ is a member of the class of so-called "Stieltjes functions" whose asymptotic power series $\sum a_nx^n$ about $x = 0$ is such that $${\operatornamewithlimits\varlimsup_{n \rightarrow \infty}} \frac{\log |a_n|}{n \log n} = r,$$ then the coefficients of the series of shifted Chebyshev polynomials on $x \in \lbrack 0, a \rbrack, \sum b_nT_n^\ast(x/a)$, satisfy the inequality $$\frac{2}{r + 2} \geq {\operatornamewithlimits\varlimsup_{n \rightarrow \infty}} \frac{\log|(\log|b_n|)|}{\log n} \geqslant 1 - \frac{r}{2}.$$ There is an intriguing relationship between this theorem and a similar rate-of-convergence theorem for Padé approximants of Stieltjes functions which is discussed below. 
            </p>
